SIMPLE: preterition
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preterition
<hw>Pre`ter*i"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praeteritio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧rition</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
passing, or going past; the state of being past.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure by which, in pretending
to pass over anything, a summary mention of it is made; <as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧I
will not say, he is valiant, he is learned, he is just</as>.⟦rdquo⟧
Called also <altname>paraleipsis</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The omission by a testator of some
one of his heirs who is entitled to a portion.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preteritive</ent>⟦br⟧
